nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.evolution.operators.mutation

Class MutationOperator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TProgram>>

  • nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.evolution.operators.mutation.MutationOperator<TProgram,TOutput,TTarget>
  • Type Parameters:
    TProgram -

    The type of programs being mutated.

    TOutput -

    The type of the program output(s).

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MacroMutationOperator, MicroMutationOperator

    public class MutationOperator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TProgram>>
implements Module

    A search operator used during evolution to mutate an individual from a population.

    The individual is mutated in place, that is a call to MutationOperator.mutate will directly modify the given individual.

    See Also:
    MutationOperator.mutate
